ce:section.ce:para:
·OH scavenging activity is a significant indicator to reflect the antioxidant ability of antioxidants. Here, the PL spectra of 2-hydroxyterephthalic acid were used to assess the ·OH scavenging activity of Al-CQDs, Al-CNSs and CNSs. As shown in Fig. 5
                        a, when 50 μL of Al-CQDs, Al-CNSs or CNSs solution (0.1 mg/mL) was added to 2 mL of the experimental solution, the PL intensity around 430 nm is significantly reduced. After calculating, the ·OH scavenging efficiency of Al-CQDs, Al-CNSs and CNSs was 72.371%, 83.842% and 67.107%, respectively. By comparing the above results, it can support that the Al doping enhances the antioxidant activity of Al-CNSs. According to the previous related reports (Table 1
                        ), it can be seen that the ·OH scavenging efficiency of as-prepared Al-CQDs is superior to most CQDs.
